# Takeaway

The key idea is to use the **Complete Binary Tree** property. If the leftmost and rightmost heights of a subtree are equal, it is a **Perfect Binary Tree**, and the number of nodes can be calculated directly using:

```text
2^height - 1
```

Otherwise, recursively count the left and right subtrees. This optimization improves the time complexity from **O(n)** to **O((log n)²)**.
